From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0060/N] globalDefinitions.hpp: HeapWord/MetaWord = 8-byte struct under purecap

The fundamental fix for the LogHeapWordSize/sizeof(HeapWord) mismatch
on CHERI purecap, replacing the temporary guarantee bypass added in
0056 (which can now be left in place harmlessly as the assertion no
longer fires).

Background. HotSpot defines:

  class HeapWordImpl;             // Opaque, never defined.
  typedef HeapWordImpl* HeapWord; // pointer to incomplete type

Heap math throughout assumes `HeapWordSize == sizeof(HeapWord) ==
1 << LogHeapWordSize == 8`. Under CHERI purecap, sizeof(any pointer)
is 16 bytes (a capability), so `sizeof(HeapWord)` becomes 16. All
heap word counts then over-multiply by 2x, leading to:

  - memset writing past mprotect bounds
  - heap-size accounting doubling
  - oop / HeapWord-size invariants breaking

The right fix under CHERI: HeapWord must remain 8 bytes. Since the
JVM never actually dereferences HeapWordImpl* (the class is opaque),
the type can be a *struct* instead of a pointer:

  struct HeapWordImpl { int64_t _word; };
  typedef HeapWordImpl HeapWord;            // sizeof == 8

`HeapWord*` is still a 16-byte capability that points to an 8-byte
struct, so pointer arithmetic (`hw + 1`) increments by 8 bytes
correctly. The change is functionally transparent because no code
dereferences a HeapWord value directly.

Same treatment for `MetaWord`. Both are wrapped in
`#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__` so the non-CHERI build is
untouched.

Downstream knock-on issues that emerged from this fix and are
addressed by 0061 + 0062:

  - 0061: BinList Block layout (16-byte ptr + 8-byte size_t = 32 B
    no longer fits in the original 2-word minimum)
  - 0062: `genCollectedHeap` guarantee `HeapWordSize == wordSize` is
    fundamentally incompatible with CHERI (8 != 16) and must be skipped

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md (patch 0060)

--- a/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/share/utilities/globalDefinitions.hpp
@@ -219,12 +219,27 @@
 //   hw += oop(hw)->foo();
 // works, where foo is a method (like size or scavenge) that returns the
 // object size.
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+// CHERI purecap: sizeof(any pointer) == 16 (capability). To keep HotSpot's
+// invariant sizeof(HeapWord) == (1 << LogHeapWordSize) == 8, define HeapWord
+// and MetaWord as 8-byte opaque structs (not pointer-to-opaque). HotSpot
+// uses HeapWord* / MetaWord* throughout (those remain 16-byte capabilities
+// that increment by sizeof(HeapWord)==8 on pointer arithmetic) and never
+// dereferences the opaque struct directly, so the change is functionally
+// transparent.
+struct HeapWordImpl { int64_t _word; };
+typedef HeapWordImpl HeapWord;
+
+struct MetaWordImpl { int64_t _word; };
+typedef MetaWordImpl MetaWord;
+#else
 class HeapWordImpl;             // Opaque, never defined.
 typedef HeapWordImpl* HeapWord;
 
 // Analogous opaque struct for metadata allocated from metaspaces.
 class MetaWordImpl;             // Opaque, never defined.
 typedef MetaWordImpl* MetaWord;
+#endif
 
 // HeapWordSize must be 2^LogHeapWordSize.
 const int HeapWordSize        = sizeof(HeapWord);
